article.headline: Illinois St. 67, Drake 45
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa. -- Osiris Eldridge scored a game-high 14 points and added 10 rebounds to lead Illinois State to a 67-45 victory against Drake on Sunday night. The Redbirds (21-5, 10-5 Missouri Valley Conference) have won three straight on the road and are in third place in the conference, two games back of first-place Northern Iowa and a game behind Creighton. Jonathan Cox led Drake (15-12, 6-9) with 11 points and Josh Young finished with 10. Landon Shipley scored eight points in the first four minutes to help Illinois State jump out to a 12-2 lead. Illinois State had a 13-point halftime lead and extended that cushion to 29 points in the second half. Emmanuel Holloway added 11 points and six assists for the Redbirds.
